      "span_text": "The second factor, the growth rate of the population immediately after the fall in fertility to replacement, reflected both differential growth by region and the departure of the initial population from the ultimate stationary composition.  concluded that spatial momentum led to population growth only when the faster growing state was overrepresented in the initial population, with the magnitude of that growth more sensitive to the speed of convergence to stationarity."
